      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "Below approximately 1800 m only a little snow is lying. In gullies and bowls above approximately 1800 m a lot of snow is lying. In the last few days sometimes deep wind slabs formed in particular in gullies and bowls and behind abrupt changes in the terrain. In some places wind slabs are lying on a hard crust. Light snowfall above approximately 1600 m: In the course of the day further wind slabs will form in particular adjacent to ridgelines and in gullies and bowls. These are mostly small."
